title: How much data to give partners
text: A potential partner requested info about my app including total downloads, MAU, user demographics (age, gender, ect), and usage time. Is it normal to share this amount of info for someone before they even sign a contract?

Need opinion on creating a password manager
text:
I am working on a project of creating a password manager which lets you generate a unique email and fake details to fill along with the password cause most password manager only let you generate a password but you are still using your main mail in all the websites

This will prevent mail spam cause you will get a separate mail account for every website you register and you can get access to it’s inbox and mail password

Also after registering you will get a private RSA Key which can’t be cracked and which won’t be stored in the server so even if whole website got hacked there is no way the hackers can retrive the passwords cause they need the private key to decrypt the password and every user will have a separate private key

What do you think of the idea should i proceed with creating it or is it just waste of time?

Ask HN: Is GitHub‘s mobile tree view navigation broken?
text:
For months, when navigating through a repo’s files on mobile, the back button is consistently broken. The URL will change, but the view doesn’t. I have to swipe back multiple times to go anywhere (and typically I end up where I didn’t expect -- multiple history items back).

The only workaround I’ve found is to literally reload the tab after tapping back. Or to not use back at all and navigate via breadcrumbs.

Is this just me? How has this not been fixed for this long? Is this a dark pattern to push people to the mobile app?
